      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HELLO CHILLI (7) goes very well at the distance with five wins and a placing from 10 starts. Below best last time at this track (23.01) in a Grade 4/5, finishing a 8 length sixth. Makes strong appeal on best. FASCINATE GEORGE (5) pinged the lids and was in the firing line early but drifted out of it when 8th at The Gardens in Grade 4/5 company. Has a good record here at this journey. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Has ability and a bold showing is expected. REAL EXPRESS (1) turned in a modest effort most recently when fifth at Richmond over 401m behind Sydney Keeping (23.12) in a Grade 4/5. Was in the money the start prior. The form out of his last race has been franked. Should play a prominent role. RUBY JUAN (6) is worth some thought after placing as favourite last start.",
